The simulation of solar cells can generally be divided into optical and electrical simulation. Good optical design is one of the main approaches for solar cells to achieve high efficiency. It includes reducing the front reflection and enhancing the internal trapping of the cell. The method of optical simulation is to calculate the carrier generation rates in the bulk, and then the three coupled differential equations of the Poisson equation, the electron and hole continuity equations are solved numerically under certain boundary conditions to calculate the electron concentration n(x)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
